  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`to_little_endian_64` [states here](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/deposit_contract/contracts/validator_registration.vy#L34) that it's inputs always fit 64-bits. To me it seems this is technically not true, albeit very unlikely to every be exploited.\r\n\r\nThis helper is used for two values: `deposit_count` and `deposit_amount`. There is an assertion for `deposit_count < 2^32-1`, however none for `deposit_amount`.\r\n\r\nThe only way to overflow `deposit_amount` is by sending a transaction with value larger than `2^64-1 * 10^9` (in wei), which is unrealistic, but given the contract already has a couple of assertions, probably the cost of an additional one wouldn't be a problem.\r\n\r\nIs this just a) missed; b) intentionally like this; c) or I have messed up something?",
